# Squeezelite arguments for the HiFi Player appliance.
# -v  enables the visualizer shared-memory export (/dev/shm/squeezelite-*)
#     which the VU-meter daemon reads. DO NOT remove -v or the VU meter stops working.
# -D  enables DSD playback. Without it squeezelite downconverts DSD to PCM; with it
#     DSD is passed bit-perfect to a DSD-capable DAC via DoP (DSD over PCM).
# -s 127.0.0.1  points to the local Lyrion Music Server.
# -o default    uses the ALSA default device. The UI wizard rewrites this to a
#               specific DAC. It uses the stable card *name*, e.g.
#               -o hw:CARD=D50s,DEV=0  (NOT -o hw:1,0 — card numbers can change
#               across reboots, the CARD= name does not). Run `aplay -l` to list.
ARGS='-o default -D -v -C 5 -s 127.0.0.1 -n OsmiumSound'
